Some things i want to achieve with this:

- remove the cli
- slim down the columns or simplify them, this might mean creating more 
enums - referring to the polars enum columns here. maybe we can identify
if there are any that are not being used
- have the config help drive the output file names, number of sims for analysis,
return periods for analysis output.
- create a very lightweight e2e test suite that contains just a few calculations
e.g. one or two rows from verisk/risklink and just one peril and lob and the 
blending factors are tested with a fixed blending factor test file etc.
- do we need to reformat any of the pipeline so that they can take specified 
file locations for the test suite to work? 
- we see dotted around 10_000 hard coded for verisk and 100_000 hard coded for risklink
these are now in the config file.
- the test suite will need to be much lighter as we are now removing the cli option
and the idea is to run the pipeline on dataiku.
- how do we also potentially do one single .collect then do fanouts, it looks 
like in this branch we are actually calling .collect on each frame. not sure if this is
necessary, at least unless we want debug mode. i wonder if there is a way to .collect
but still do all the debug output?
